type: software
title: "Computational Framework for Cereal Extrusion Optimization"
abstract: >
  A computational framework integrating LLM-assisted data collection pipelines,
  mechanistic kinetic models, a Random Forest bioactivity predictor, and global
  optimization to identify extrusion conditions that maximize nutrient density
  (NRF9.3) and antioxidant capacity (FRAP) for breakfast cereal formulations.
